Write a program to:

Compare two numbers
Display grade based on marks
Program
# Number comparison
a = int(input("Enter first number: "))
b = int(input("Enter second number: "))

if a > b:
    print("First number is greater")
elif a < b:
    print("Second number is greater")
else:
    print("Both numbers are equal")

# Grading system
marks = int(input("\nEnter marks: "))

if marks >= 90:
    grade = "A"
elif marks >= 75:
    grade = "B"
elif marks >= 60:
    grade = "C"
elif marks >= 50:
    grade = "D"
else:
    grade = "Fail"

print("Grade:", grade)

Output

Enter first number: 10
Enter second number: 20
Second number is greater

Enter marks: 85
Grade: B
